{"search_data": "Central PM Scholarship Scheme (PMSS) 2020 Assistance Hiked for Boys & Girls Central govt. approves hike in assistance rates for Prime Minister Scholarship Scheme (PMSS) 2019-2020, Rs. 2500 for boys & Rs. 3000 for girls in Pradhan Mantri Scholarship Yojana, major changes approved in PM Scholarship Scheme under the National Defence Fund including enhanced scholarships for wards of police personnel martyred in terror or Maoist attacksTable of Contents  Prime Minister Scholarship Scheme Assistance RaisedMajor Changes in PM Scholarship Yojana 2020 ApprovedNational Defence Fund for PM\u2019s Scholarship Scheme 2020Modi 2.0 First Cabinet DecisionsPrime Minister Scholarship Scheme Assistance RaisedThe first cabinet meeting of second tenure of Modi government has taken a very important decision for the welfare of families of martyred policemen. Union govt. is committed towards the welfare of the defence personnels and to enable them to lead a life of dignity as 1 member of their family has sacrificed his / her life for the country. Now the children of martyr policemen (died in terrorist, maoist attack) will get an increased amount of scholarship.On assuming office, the first decision that PM Narendra Modi took is approval to a major change in the Prime Minister\u2019s Scholarship Scheme under the National Defence Fund. The rates of scholarship have been increased from Rs 2,000 per month to Rs 2,500 per month for boys and from Rs 2,250 per month to Rs 3,000 per month for girls.Our Government\u2019s first decision dedicated to those who protect India!Major changes approved in PM\u2019s Scholarship Scheme under the National Defence Fund including enhanced scholarships for wards of police personnel martyred in terror or Maoist attacks. https://t.co/Vm90BD77hm pic.twitter.com/iXhFNlBCIc\u2014 Narendra Modi (@narendramodi) May 31, 2019The first few decisions of the Government are dedicated to those who feed India and protect India. pic.twitter.com/tAkT99nOs1\u2014 PMO India (@PMOIndia) June 1, 2019Major Changes in PM Scholarship Yojana 2020 ApprovedThe other changes made under PM Scholarship Yojana are as follows:-The scope of PM scholarship scheme is extended to the wards of state police officials who are / were martyred during terrorists or naxal attacks.The quota of new scholarships for wards of state police officials would be 500 in a single year. The Ministry of Home Affairs will be the nodal ministry in this regard.Previously, the children of martyrs like Tukaram Omble (killed during Mumbai terror attack) were not eligible for scholarship under PMSS scheme. This new move will remove this anomaly and help families of all those deceased while fighting terror/naxals in state police forces.The changes under PM Scholarship Yojana 2019-20 comes in line with the PM\u2019s vision for India\u2019s safety, security and the well-being of those who protect the nation.National Defence Fund for PM\u2019s Scholarship Scheme 2020National Defence Fund (NDF) was set up in FY 1962 to take charge of the voluntary donations in cash and kind received for promotion of the national defense effort and to decide on their utilization. NDF is currently used for the welfare of the members of the armed forces, paramilitary forces and Railway Protection Force (RPF) and their dependents.The Prime Minister\u2019s Scholarship Scheme (PMSS) is now being being implemented to encourage technical and post-graduate education for widows and wards of the deceased/ex-service personnel of armed forces and paramilitary forces and RPF. Under PMSS, every year new scholarships are given to 5,500 wards of armed forces, 2,000 wards of paramilitary forces and for 150 wards of RPF.For more details, visit the official website at http://www.desw.gov.in/scholarshipModi 2.0 First Cabinet Decisions\u2014 PM Kisan Scheme for All Farmers \u2014 PM Modi Farmers Pension Scheme Approved \u2014 PM Traders & Shopkeepers Pension Scheme  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Re